abstract: Intra-Cellular Therapies Inc said on Monday its lead drug to treat schizophrenia in adults has received approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, sending its shares soaring 85%.
snippet: Intra-Cellular Therapies Inc said on Monday its lead drug to treat schizophrenia in adults has received approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, sending its shares soaring 85%.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Intra-Cellular Therapies Inc said on Monday its lead drug to treat schizophrenia in adults has received approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, sending its shares soaring 85%.
headline_main: FDA Approves Intra-Cellullar's Schizophrenia Drug, Shares Soar 85%
headline_print_headline: FDA Approves Intra-Cellullar's Schizophrenia Drug, Shares Soar 85%

abstract: Hundreds of people joined a protest on Monday against Myanmar’s police after the force broke the law by revealing the name of the child victim of a high profile rape case following the acquittal of a suspect.
snippet: Hundreds of people joined a protest on Monday against Myanmar’s police after the force broke the law by revealing the name of the child victim of a high profile rape case following the acquittal of a suspect.
lead_paragraph: YANGON — Hundreds of people joined a protest on Monday against Myanmar’s police after the force broke the law by revealing the name of the child victim of a high profile rape case following the acquittal of a suspect.
headline_main: Hundreds Rally Against Myanmar Police Over Child Rape Case
headline_print_headline: Hundreds Rally Against Myanmar Police Over Child Rape Case

abstract: The mayor of Burundi's capital says at least 15 people have been killed by landslides caused by heavy rains over the weekend.
snippet: The mayor of Burundi's capital says at least 15 people have been killed by landslides caused by heavy rains over the weekend.
lead_paragraph: NAIROBI, Kenya — The mayor of Burundi's capital says at least 15 people have been killed by landslides caused by heavy rains over the weekend.
headline_main: Mayor Says Landslides Kill at Least 15 in Burundi's Capital
headline_print_headline: Mayor Says Landslides Kill at Least 15 in Burundi's Capital

abstract: Drug overdose patients rushed  to some emergency rooms in New York's Hudson Valley are asked a series of questions: Do you have stable housing? Do you have food? Times and location of overdoses are noted, too.
snippet: Drug overdose patients rushed  to some emergency rooms in New York's Hudson Valley are asked a series of questions: Do you have stable housing? Do you have food? Times and location of overdoses are noted, too.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY, N.Y. — Drug overdose patients rushed to some emergency rooms in New York's Hudson Valley are asked a series of questions: Do you have stable housing? Do you have food? Times and location of overdoses are noted, too.
headline_main: To Battle Opioid Crisis, Some Track Overdoses in Real Time
headline_print_headline: To Battle Opioid Crisis, Some Track Overdoses in Real Time

abstract: Christmas cheer rang out through Bethlehem's Manger Square on Monday as pilgrims and worshippers flocked to the city revered as Jesus's birthplace and locals made final preparations for this year's festivities.
snippet: Christmas cheer rang out through Bethlehem's Manger Square on Monday as pilgrims and worshippers flocked to the city revered as Jesus's birthplace and locals made final preparations for this year's festivities.
lead_paragraph: BETHLEHEM, West Bank — Christmas cheer rang out through Bethlehem's Manger Square on Monday as pilgrims and worshippers flocked to the city revered as Jesus's birthplace and locals made final preparations for this year's festivities.
headline_main: Carols and Bells in Bethlehem as Christmas Draws Near

abstract: Thailand's Constitutional Court says it will rule on a sedition complaint that claims a popular opposition political party is linked to the Illuminati, which conspiracy theorists say secretly seeks world domination.
snippet: Thailand's Constitutional Court says it will rule on a sedition complaint that claims a popular opposition political party is linked to the Illuminati, which conspiracy theorists say secretly seeks world domination.
lead_paragraph: BANGKOK — Thailand's Constitutional Court says it will rule on a sedition complaint that claims a popular opposition political party is linked to the Illuminati, which conspiracy theorists say secretly seeks world domination.
headline_main: Thai Court to Rule on Case Linking Opposition to Illuminati
headline_print_headline: Thai Court to Rule on Case Linking Opposition to Illuminati

abstract: Gen. Ahmed Gaïd Salah arranged the ouster of the country’s longtime president this year, while cracking down on a protest movement that demanded broader change.
snippet: Gen. Ahmed Gaïd Salah arranged the ouster of the country’s longtime president this year, while cracking down on a protest movement that demanded broader change.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — Algeria’s de facto ruler, Gen. Ahmed Gaïd Salah, who this year managed the ouster of one president and the ascent of another amid deep civil unrest, died on Monday, according to the state news agency and Algerian press reports.

abstract: Brookefield Infrastructure Partners LP will buy telecommunications company Cincinnati Bell Inc for about $529.42 million (406.81 million pounds), the companies said on Monday.
snippet: Brookefield Infrastructure Partners LP will buy telecommunications company Cincinnati Bell Inc for about $529.42 million (406.81 million pounds), the companies said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Brookefield Infrastructure Partners LP will buy telecommunications company Cincinnati Bell Inc for about $529.42 million (406.81 million pounds), the companies said on Monday.

abstract: A Syrian war monitoring group said Monday that an Israeli missile strike overnight near the capital of Damascus killed at least three foreigners, who were most likely Iranians.

abstract: A joint venture of Galliford Try and Balfour Beatty Plc is in advanced discussions to settle claims related to the construction of a motorway project in Aberdeen, the British companies said on Monday.
